---
description: SentinelOps repository guidance
alwaysApply: true
---
This repository is the source for SentinelOps, a plug-and-play incident and operations copilot.

- Keep CLI, repo attachment, and generated agent/editor integrations aligned.
- Treat `.sentinelops/project.toml` as the repo-local single-config contract when changing attach/runtime behavior.
- Keep Claude Code skills, `CLAUDE.md`, and other generated agent files aligned with the CLI flow.
- Update README and repo docs when install, version, production, or validation flows change.
- When operational context matters, prefer SentinelOps-specific docs and commands over generic advice.
